<item>
            <title>[SPARK-29105] SHS may delete driver log file of in progress application</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-29105</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s an issue with how the SHS cleans driver logs that is similar to the problem of event logs: because the file size is not updated when you write to it, the SHS fails to detect activity and thus may delete the file while it&apos;s still being written to.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-24787&quot; title=&quot;Events being dropped at an alarming rate due to hsync being slow for eventLogging&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-24787&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-24787&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added a workaround in the SHS so that it can detect that situation for in-progress apps, replacing the previous solution which was too slow for event logs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But that doesn&apos;t work for driver logs because they do not follow the same pattern (different file names for in-progress files), and thus would require the SHS to open the driver log files on every scan, which is expensive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The old approach (using the &lt;tt&gt;hsync&lt;/tt&gt; API) seems to be a good match for the driver logs, though, which don&apos;t slow down the listener bus like event logs do.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
